<h2>Fleet building steps</h2>
<ol>
    <li>
        <div class="container">
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col col-4">
                    <a href="../images/NameFleet.png" target="_blank">
                        <img src="../images/NameFleet.png" class="img-thumbnail" alt="Name the Fleet">
                    </a>
                </div>
                <div class="col col-8">
                    First pick a name for your fleet that will be entered into the tournament
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </li>
    <li>
        Select a name for your Ship
    </li>
    <li>
        Pick a Ship Type card
    </li>
    <li>
        Determine which, if any, Modifiers that you wish to apply to your ship
    </li>
    <li>
        Determine the number of cannons to add to your ship. Cannons are assumed to be evenly distributed between sides of the ship, 
        so you must choose an even number of cannons
    </li>
    <li>
        <div class="container">
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col col-4">
                    <a href="../images/AddShipToFleet.png" target="_blank">
                        <img src="../images/AddShipToFleet.png" class="img-thumbnail" alt="Add Ship to Fleet">
                    </a>
                </div>
                <div class="col col-8">
                    Select the total number of crew for your ship. You must choose to at least add the minimum amount for the Ship Type, however
                    it is highly recommended that you add at least the Ideal Crew value of pirates otherwise your ship will not operate at full capacity.
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </li>
</ol>

<h2>Ship Cost</h2>
<p>
    The following is the way that a Ships cost is determined.
</p>
<ol>
    <li>
        The base cost for your ship will be the Sale Price listed on the Ship Type card
    </li>
    <li>
        Adjust the base cost of the ship based on any Modifier cards being played on the Ship
    </li>
    <li>
        The standard cost of a cannon is 20 per cannon
    </li>
    <li>
        Adjust the cost of the cannon by any Modifier cards on the Ship
    </li>
    <li>
        Multiply the adjusted cost by the number of cannons added to the Ship
    </li>
    <li>
        The standard cost of a crew member is 10 per crew member, and assumes food, wages and everything need for the crew
    </li>
    <li>
        Adjust the cost per Crew based on any Modifier cards
    </li>
    <li>
        Multiply the Adjusted cost by the total number of Crew added to the Ship
    </li>
    <li>
        Sum up the cost of the Ship, Crew and Cannons
    </li>
    <li>
        Apply any adjustments based on the Modifier cards in play that do not explicitly modify the Ship, Crew or Cannon costs 
    </li>
</ol>

